**Definition**
A footer in jQuery Mobile is a bottom-of-page layout widget used to display navigation controls, copyright text, or persistent action buttons.

**Types**

* Standard footer
* Fixed footer
* Themed footer
* Footer with navbar

**Working**
The footer is created using a `<div>` with `data-role="footer"`. jQuery Mobile styles it and positions it at the bottom of the page. When fixed, it stays visible while scrolling.

**Diagrams (text)**

```
-------------------
[ Page Content ]
[     Footer     ]
```

**Advantages**

* Provides consistent bottom navigation
* Supports navbars inside the footer
* Can remain fixed for quick access

**Disadvantages**

* Fixed footer reduces visible content
* Too many footer buttons can clutter UI

**Examples**

```html
<div data-role="footer">
  <h4>Â© 2024 My App</h4>
</div>
```

Footer with navbar:

```html
<div data-role="footer">
  <div data-role="navbar">
    <ul>
      <li><a href="#home">Home</a></li>
      <li><a href="#about">About</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>
```

**Short code snippets**
Fixed footer:

```html
<div data-role="footer" data-position="fixed">
```

**Applications**

* Navigation menus
* Copyright information
* Persistent action buttons
* Bottom toolbars in mobile apps
